Description: Multi-WAN firewall, DHCP server, VPN and router (full appliance)
 NetFirewall is an opinionated home/SOHO firewall stack built from scratch on
 .NET 10 + PostgreSQL. It bundles a hardened privileged daemon, a web UI, a
 DHCP server, a WAN failover monitor, a console TUI for offline / break-glass
 administration, and a deployment doctor.
 .
 The .NET binaries are published self-contained — the runtime travels inside
 the package, so there is NO dependency on dotnet-runtime / aspnetcore-runtime
 or the Microsoft APT repository. libicu is required because the application
 does culture-aware work (no InvariantGlobalization).
 .
 This package installs:
   * /opt/netfirewall/{daemon,web,dhcp-server,tui,doctor,migrations} binaries
   * /opt/netfirewall/templates/{daemon,web,dhcp}.env.template — env templates
   * /opt/netfirewall/migrations/sql/migrations + /opt/netfirewall/seeds — SQL
   * systemd units: netfirewall-{daemon,web,dhcp,bootstrap,firstboot}
   * /usr/local/bin/{netfirewall-tui,netfirewall-doctor,netfirewall-bootstrap,
     netfirewall-firstboot} + manpage + bash completion
 .
 Provisioning is split in two so that flashing one appliance image to many
 machines never shares one master key or DB password:
 .
   * postinst (package configure time) does ONLY deterministic, secret-free
     work: creates the `netfirewall` group and `netfirewall-web` service user,
     lays out directories with the right modes, installs systemd units, sysctl
     and tmpfiles drop-ins, and enables (but does NOT start) the services. The
     env files are placed verbatim from the templates and still contain the
     __REPLACE__ / __REPLACE_MASTER_KEY__ placeholders. NO secrets are written
     and NO database is touched at this stage.
   * netfirewall-firstboot.service runs ONCE on the first real boot of the
     installed system. It generates a per-appliance AES-256 master key and a
     random local PostgreSQL password, initialises the local cluster, creates
     the role and database, fills BOTH env files with the SAME master key (a
     diff-assert guarantees they match — see docs/master-key.md), runs the
     migrations, applies the seeds, starts the daemon and web, and runs the
     doctor. After it succeeds it drops /var/lib/netfirewall/.provisioned so it
     never runs again.
 .
 First-time configuration via the web UI requires a bootstrap token, printed
 to journalctl on the first start with an empty users table. See
 /usr/share/doc/netfirewall/README.Debian for the unattended-install path.
